                           ENDANGERED SPECIES ACT
                   STATUS REVIEWS AND LISTING INFORMATION

   The National Marine Fisheries Service, Northwest Region is responsible
   for conducting Endangered Species Act (ESA) status reviews for marine
   and anadromous fishes, including 5 species of salmon - Chinook, Chum,
   Coho, Pink, Sockeye - and Steelhead (trout).  Below are links to
   detailed information about each species - maps, Federal Register
   notices, and listing status.


